# .aidocs/project-init.aidocs - /project Contract

Read order
1) `AIDOCS.md`
2) `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
3) linked shared docs

Pre-edit checks
- Resolve project root.
- If no git repo: init + initial commit.
- Ensure remote exists; if missing, try `gh repo create <name> --private --source . --remote origin --push`.
- If remote creation fails, STOP and ask for remote/repo target.
- Verify upstream tracking; STOP on failure.

Portable system deployment (default)
- `/project` must vendor a self-contained runtime system into the target project so it works on another machine without root installer files.
- Copy into project root (create if missing):
  - `AIDOCS.md`
  - `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
  - linked shared docs required by the index (including memory protocol + project-init contract)
  - `.opencode/command/project.md` and `.opencode/command/archive.md`
  - `.claude/commands/project.md` and `.claude/commands/archive.md`
- Generate/refresh project `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md` with project-local relative routing (no absolute host-specific paths).
- If any required source artifact is missing, STOP and ask before partial deployment.
- For already initialized projects, prefer `/project-update` to refresh system artifacts without rerunning full init.

Analysis
- Discover project docs/router + relevant README/spec docs.
- Analyze build/runtime/db artifacts (read-only DB interrogation proposals only).
- Skip docs->code vs code->docs decision tree for now.

Memory bootstrap (template-first)
- Copy missing files/dirs from `.aidocs/templates/memory/**` to `/.MEMORY/**`.
- Required canonical files/dirs:
  - `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/policy/*`
  - `/.MEMORY/architecture/*`
  - `/.MEMORY/decisions/DECISIONS_LOG.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/operations/*`
  - `/.MEMORY/domains/`
  - `/.MEMORY/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/daily/archive/`

First-init extraction
- Sources (order): root shared docs -> project entry files -> project docs/router -> relevant README/spec docs.
- Ingest and restructure internal docs into canonical memory categories.
- Build topic map and create/update `/.MEMORY/domains/<topic>.md`.
- Merge/edit only (no duplicate append-only content).
- Output ingestion coverage: read files, skipped files, reasons, mapping.

Routing update
- Ensure project `AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md` route to `/.MEMORY/*`.
- Keep entry files short.
- Routers must point to project-local `AIDOCS.md` + `.aidocs/index.aidocs`.

Archive behavior
- `/archive` promotes from `/.MEMORY/daily/*` into canonical categories with merge semantics.
- Processed logs move to `/.MEMORY/daily/archive/`.

NOW.md initialization contract
- Initialize `/.MEMORY/NOW.md` with queue-oriented sections:
  - `Mission`
  - `Active`
  - `Upcoming (ordered)`
  - `Blockers/Risks`
  - `Resume Steps`
  - `Done/Recent`
- If task plan is multi-step, prefill `Upcoming` with at least 3 items when available.
